Requirements should come from 3 SOURCES:
SOURCE 1 - DOCUMENTS: ✅ Every major concept from documents has requirements ✅ Quantitative data reflected ✅ Tools/systems mentioned have integration requirements ✅ Pain points have solution requirements ✅ Each has source citation
SOURCE 2 - INSTRUCTIONS: ✅ All requested features have FRs ✅ All modules described have FRs ✅ All goals addressable by requirements ✅ Each cites instruction text
SOURCE 3 - INFERENCE + WEB RESEARCH: ✅ Technical infrastructure requirements present ✅ Security/auth if user data mentioned ✅ Industry standards referenced ✅ Missing requirements from analogous systems ✅ Each has rationale
RED FLAGS (incomplete): ❌ No stakeholders/actors from documents ❌ No requirements for volumes/metrics mentioned ❌ Features from instructions ignored ❌ Missing technical infrastructure ❌ No security when sensitive data mentioned ❌ Industry standards not incorporated
